content.text: Recent completed items in the elizaOS/eliza repository include several bugfixes, features, and other improvements. Bugfixes addressed build issues for Discord plugin and messaging service after a merge conflict (#4552), TEE updates for CI (#4572), and updated Telegram messageManager tests to expect MarkdownV2 (#4570). Feature additions include adding commit SHA to CLI cache action (#4571), support for third-party plugin installation (#4568), and upgrades to the CLI agent command (#4560). Other changes involved removing REST /ping for websocket status checks in the client (#4551), returning to regular dev command (#4566), using the latest v2 plugin list for tests (#4564), and enabling strict types with adjusted guards for the Telegram plugin (#4559).

Several pull requests have been submitted to the elizaOS/eliza repository. PR #4573 by Samarthsinghal28 adds a Polygon Plugin. PR #4574 by Y4NK33420 implements Polygon Gas Oracle Integration. PR #4552 by 0xbbjoker fixes build issues for the Discord plugin and service mess after merge conflicts. PR #4558 by ChristopherTrimboli fixes the Create room API. PR #4575 by HarshModi2005 addresses Issue 451.

Three issues have been reported in the elizaOS/eliza repository. Issue #4562 by samgermain requests to make a publish to npm. Issue #4561 by K1mc4n reports an error from CI activity. Issue #4565, also by K1mc4n, indicates a problem with a missing path 'packages/docs/i18n/readme/'.

From May 13-14, 2025, the GitHub repository elizaos/eliza saw significant activity with 16 new pull requests (10 of which were merged), 3 new issues opened, and 17 active contributors participating in the project.
